General.Name: Macquarie Bank Ltd Pref
General.Description: Macquarie Bank Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides a range of commercial banking and retail financial services primarily in Australia. The company operates through Banking and Financial Services (BFS), Commodities and Global Markets (CGM) segments. The BFS segment offers a range of personal banking, wealth management, and business banking products and services to retail clients, advisers, brokers, and business clients. The CGM segment provides capital and financing, risk management, market access, physical execution, and logistics solutions to its various client base across commodities, financial markets, and asset finance. It operates the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and the Asia Pacific. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Sydney, Australia. Macquarie Bank Limited operates as a subsidiary of Macquarie B.H. Pty Limited.
